Hepatitis - Russia & Belarus: update, 18 Dec 2000 20001218.2218
Hepatitis - Russia (North Ossetia) 20001204.2111
Date: Wed 14 Feb 2001 09:38:43 +0200
From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON Database, 14 Feb 2001
<http://www.cynifo.com>

The following background data on hepatitis A in the Russian Federation were
abstracted from the GIDEON Database <http://www.cynifo.com>:
Year / Rate (per 100 000) / cases reported
1990 / 204.3 / -
1991 / 165.5 / -
1992 / 117.9 / 173,845
1993 / 1098 / -
1994 / 111.2 / -
1995 / 122.6 / -
1996 / 86.9 / 108 000
1997 / 50.1 / 73 713 (40% below age 15-years of age)
1998 / 33.8 / 49 715
1999 / 30.6 / -
2000 / 15.9 / -
Other relevant information:
(1) 43.7% of Muscovites are seropositive (1994).
(2) Clusters reported during 2000 (all related to drinking water) included:
- an outbreak (34 teenagers hospitalized) in Khabarovsk;
- an unrelated outbreak in Khabarovsk resulting in 40 hospitalizations;
- 67 patients hospitalized in North Ossetia and Vladikavkaz.
--
Stephen Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
